Young students who want to get their pre-requisites out of the way cheaper before transferring to a major University. Working Class Students looking for professional development, older folks looking for a degree, or career change... pretty much anyone looking to attend a reputable college at an affordable price and wants to feel like they belong.
Childcare on campus for those students with kids.
There are a lot of family activities for students with families, and a plethora of sports, entertainment, clubs and activities to suit any student at any age.
The cafeteria is nice and has quality food at reasonable prices.
Stay on schedule and don't give up!!

Tacoma Community College is an excellent school full of diversity, culture, and student activity. The classes and schedules are realistic and doable. The faculty and staff are of the up-most quality and truly care about the success of their students.

In three sentences tacoma community college is diverse with many cultures and ages. the courses offered are good, however, i have experience both good and bad teachers. unfortunately though, it is difficult to accomplish anything through the office administration and desk workers aren't very willing to put in effort above what is expected.
